London Bike Sharing Data Exploration¶

by Beijia(Frances) Yu¶

Investigation Overview¶

I selected bike sharing dataset in order to investigate bike hiring by people. There are a lot of different variables and the main focus is to find out how these variables will affect the bike hiring on the project.

Dataset Overview¶

In this dataset, it contains 17414 records. It includes the following data types: string, integer, float and boolean. Some variables describe the weather condition: real_temperature, humidity as well as wind_speed. Some are about when the sharing was happening: timestamp, is_holiday, is_weekend, season_code, date, year, season.

The Distribution of Weather Conditions¶

  • Among 17414 records in the dataset, over 6000 records are associated with clear weather. More than 7500 bike sharings was done in cloudy days.
  • In other words, sharing bikes is most popular, at least 77.5%, when the weather is nice

Weather Condition & Shared Counts¶

  • The following plot further proves that sharing bikes are most popular in good weather condition
  • The highest median value of shared counts is when weather code = 1 (Clear). On the meantime, people seldomly share bikes when there is snowfall.
  • The median values for when it is cloudy or there is a light rain are about the same

plt.show()

Weather Condition, Shared Counts, Is Weekend & Season¶

  • Most of the time, people uses shared bikes more often on weekdays than on weekends.
  • In certain circumstances, like in certain season or certain weather condition, people do use shared bikes on weekends more often than on weekdays.

Effects of Weather Conditions on Bike Sharings¶

  • All of temperature, humidity, wind speed can have an impact on bike sharings.
  • In addition, each of them results in different distributions of bike sharings as we can see from the following plots
